e the result of environmental stress when foraging in an urban area. The causal agents of alopecia in bats are still not fully known, and it is probably a multifactorial phenomenon.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Hern\u00e1ndez-Aguilar, Itandehui", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Santos-Moreno, Antonio", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lorenzo, Consuelo", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/65cc50ba38448285abba6c93c9517c79", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/7e7fa8838ac29014428301f13b0621f2807b84d2826b9b93791f81335221f36e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/WKH42QJ3", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/WKH42QJ3", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/05fd0b002663f751be1e41af04a41f45!/b42062-44558", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "title": "Acta Chiropterologica", "volume": "25"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/65cc50ba38448285abba6c93c9517c79"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:WKH42QJ3"}, {"identifier": "10.3161/15081109ACC2023.25.1.009"}], "communities": [{"id": "biosyslit"}, {"id": "batlit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type